{
  "text": "Chronic atypical neutrophilic dermatosis with lipodystrophy and elevated temperature (CANDLE) syndrome was first described in the scientific literature in 2010 [CITATION_1] . A review of the literature reveals that to date this extremely rare syndrome has been reported in only 14 patients worldwide; seven males and seven females [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Most patients developed symptoms of the disease before the age of 6 months 3 .",
